orm at the Unity and Freedom Forum at the Hilton Pasadena, in [[Pasadena, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2019/05/31/bernie-sanders-blasts-trump-as-racist-over-immigration-in-california/1306282001/|title=Bernie Sanders blasts Trump as 'racist' at forum on immigration|work=USA Today|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190601032804/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2019/05/31/bernie-sanders-blasts-trump-as-racist-over-immigration-in-california/1306282001/|archive-date=June 1, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=June 8, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"auto19\">{{cite web|url=https://firmaction.org/presidentialforum|title=Unity & Freedom Presidential Forum|website=FIRM Action|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604001406/https://firmaction.org/presidentialforum|archive-date=June 4, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=June 8, 2019}}</ref>\n*'''May 31-June 2:''' California State Democratic Convention, a major \"cattle call\" event attended by most major candidates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cadem.org/events/2019-california-democratic-party-state-convention-may-31-june-2-2019|title=2019 California Democratic Party State Convention, May 31 - June 2, 2019|website=California Democratic Party}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-2020-democratic-candidates-president-california-party-convention-20190603-story.html|title=14 Democratic presidential candidates give California its Cinderella moment|first=Mark Z.|last=Barabak|first2=Melanie|last2=Mason|website=latimes.com}}</ref> Joe Biden is a no-show at the event, attending a [[Human Rights Campaign]] event in Ohio at the same time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/03/politics/2020-democrats-california-progressives-joe-biden/index.html|title=Joe Biden's rift with progressives on display as he skips California Democratic convention|first=Eric|last=Bradner|website=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://poli